e: D: responds to unexpected events adequately, can concentrate, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously, regarded as arrogant, relatively weak leadership skills. No explicit teamwork. B: very conscientious, handles stress well, good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills, can be grumpy, uncooperative, pretentious, sometimes wrong tone. No explicit decision-making under pressure beyond stress handling. So we can answer: we have no additional info beyond what's listed. So we can respond that we don't have further attributes.\n\nWe also need to give our vote. Based on current evidence, candidate C still best. So vote Candidate C.\n\nWe should also maybe ask if any agent has more info on D's teamwork or B's decision-making. But we already answered that we have none. Could ask others if they have any info. But we can also just answer the questions.\n\nThus public message: respond to agent_1's request: provide any additional attributes for D teamwork/leadership and B decision-making under pressure. State we have none beyond listed. Also reaffirm evaluation and vote.\n\nProceed."}
